results.occurrenceRemarks: Amazing!  You could basically walk up to them and they didn't care (there was a very short, insubstantial rope fence).  Constant noise and movement of birds squabbling, feeding their young, doing some kind of ritual head-waving dance, ferrying in small branches, running for takeoff, and landing ungracefully and straight down with their big flat feet fanned.

South Bruny National Park, South Bruny National Park lies at the southern tip of Bruny Island off the southeast coast of Tasmania. The park encompasses all of the coastline and some of the hinterland between Fluted Cape and the southern part of Great Taylors Bay.

Adventure Bay, Adventure Bay on southeast Bruny Island incorporates a series of beaches and adjacent  stands of fairly open Eucalypt forest . After passing Cemetery Bluff the first beach is known colloquially as "cemetery" beach. After Two Tree Point comes Barkers beach which is separated from Adventure Bay beach by a headland. After the main beach, which is several kilometres in length, there is a rocky shore for a kilometre or so before East Cove beach, which leads into Fluted Cape national park. Coolangatta and Lockleys roads lead inland into wet Eucalypt and rainforest.
